WEBVTT

1
00:00:54.182 --> 00:00:56.267
[cicadas chirrup]

2
00:00:57.226 --> 00:00:59.312
[muttering]

3
00:02:22.476 --> 00:02:24.937
- Peter.
- [gasps]

4
00:02:27.731 --> 00:02:30.901
You could not watch
even one hour with me?

5
00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:35.405
- Master. what has happened to you?
- Should I call the others. Lord?

6
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:40.243
No. John.
I don't want them to see me like this.

7
00:02:40.327 --> 00:02:42.871
Are you in danger? Should we flee. Master?

8
00:02:42.954 --> 00:02:45.498
Stay here. Watch...

9
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.669
...pray.

10
00:02:56.718 --> 00:02:58.803
[breathes heavily]

11
00:03:03.307 --> 00:03:05.393
What is wrong with him?

12
00:03:06.644 --> 00:03:08.729
He seems afraid.

13
00:03:09.397 --> 00:03:12.358
He had spoken about danger while we ate...

14
00:03:13.526 --> 00:03:16.028
He mentioned betrayal and...

15
00:03:16.112 --> 00:03:18.197
[bird screeches]

16
00:03:27.331 --> 00:03:29.416
[footsteps approach]

17
00:03:37.466 --> 00:03:39.009
30.

18
00:03:39.092 --> 00:03:41.386
30. Judas.

19
00:03:41.470 --> 00:03:45.557
That was the agreement between me
and you?

20
00:03:46.349 --> 00:03:48.435
Yes.

21
00:03:51.354 --> 00:03:53.440
[jangle]

22
00:04:02.615 --> 00:04:04.701
[clattering]

23
00:04:32.561 --> 00:04:34.646
Where?

24
00:04:35.564 --> 00:04:37.649
Where is he?

25
00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:50.245
[breathes heavily]

26
00:04:57.002 --> 00:04:59.087
[gasps]

27
00:05:11.766 --> 00:05:14.310
Hear me. Father.

28
00:05:16.854 --> 00:05:21.692
Rise up. defend me.

29
00:05:25.946 --> 00:05:31.368
Save me from the traps they set for me.

30
00:05:52.806 --> 00:05:56.142
Do you really believe...

31
00:05:56.226 --> 00:06:02.774
...that one man can
bear the full burden of sin?

32
00:06:03.692 --> 00:06:05.777
Shelter me. O Lord.

33
00:06:07.904 --> 00:06:09.989
I trust in you.

34
00:06:13.159 --> 00:06:16.621
In you I take refuge.

35
00:06:20.041 --> 00:06:27.214
No one man can carry this burden.
I tell you.

36
00:06:28.382 --> 00:06:30.468
It is far too heavy.

37
00:06:31.385 --> 00:06:35.514
Saving their souls is too costly.

38
00:06:36.223 --> 00:06:39.435
No one. Ever.

39
00:06:40.477 --> 00:06:42.563
No.

40
00:06:43.689 --> 00:06:45.774
Never.

41
00:06:46.817 --> 00:06:51.655
Father. you can do all things.

42
00:06:54.366 --> 00:06:59.120
If it is possible.
let this chalice pass from me...

43
00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:08.963
But let your will be done. not mine.

44
00:07:11.466 --> 00:07:13.551
[gentle gasp]

45
00:07:27.607 --> 00:07:29.692
[gentle thud]

46
00:07:36.949 --> 00:07:39.034
Who is your father?

47
00:07:40.703 --> 00:07:42.788
[Jesus muttering]

48
00:07:45.708 --> 00:07:49.211
- [Satan] Who are you?
- [continues muttering]

49
00:07:56.093 --> 00:07:58.178
[ominous music]

50
00:08:16.946 --> 00:08:19.032
[continues muttering]

51
00:08:27.623 --> 00:08:29.709
[dramatic music]

52
00:08:51.605 --> 00:08:53.690
[exhales]

53
00:09:10.123 --> 00:09:12.208
[loud thwack]

54
00:09:18.465 --> 00:09:20.300
Ah.

55
00:09:25.847 --> 00:09:27.932
[flames crackle]

56
00:09:46.617 --> 00:09:48.702
Who are you looking for?

57
00:09:53.540 --> 00:09:56.085
We're looking for Jesus of Nazareth.

58
00:09:59.171 --> 00:10:00.589
[grunts]

59
00:10:00.672 --> 00:10:02.758
I am he.

60
00:10:08.722 --> 00:10:10.807
[Biblical music]

61
00:10:21.526 --> 00:10:23.611
[flames roar]

62
00:10:30.785 --> 00:10:32.870
Hail. Rabbi!

63
00:10:45.675 --> 00:10:48.177
Judas...

64
00:10:48.260 --> 00:10:51.764
...you betray the Son of Man
with a kiss?

65
00:11:17.831 --> 00:11:19.916
[grunts]

66
00:11:20.834 --> 00:11:22.919
[soldiers shout]

67
00:11:24.254 --> 00:11:26.339
[grunts]

68
00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:31.845
[thwack]

69
00:11:31.928 --> 00:11:34.013
[grunts]

70
00:11:36.057 --> 00:11:38.142
- [thwack]
- Agh!

71
00:11:41.813 --> 00:11:43.397
[dramatic music]

72
00:11:43.481 --> 00:11:45.566
- [thwack]
- [grunts]

73
00:11:51.947 --> 00:11:54.033
[metallic clanking]

74
00:11:55.493 --> 00:11:57.369
- [clunk]
- Agh!

75
00:11:57.453 --> 00:11:59.872
- [squelch]
- Argh!

76
00:12:02.708 --> 00:12:04.793
[chains rattle]

77
00:12:06.086 --> 00:12:08.172
[gasps]

78
00:12:19.433 --> 00:12:21.518
[groans]

79
00:12:29.359 --> 00:12:31.444
[gasps]

80
00:12:34.864 --> 00:12:36.950
[gasps]

81
00:12:41.204 --> 00:12:43.289
Ohh... Ohh...

82
00:12:53.257 --> 00:12:55.343
Peter!

83
00:12:56.677 --> 00:12:58.763
Put it down!

84
00:12:58.846 --> 00:13:04.059
Those who live by the sword
shall die by the sword.

85
00:13:12.901 --> 00:13:14.987
Put it down.

86
00:13:16.405 --> 00:13:18.115
[clatters]

87
00:13:18.198 --> 00:13:20.283
- [thwack]
- Ohh.

88
00:13:46.184 --> 00:13:48.269
- [metallic rattle]
- [groans]

89
00:13:48.352 --> 00:13:50.313
Malchus! Get up!

90
00:13:50.396 --> 00:13:53.691
We've got him. Let's go!

91
00:14:07.913 --> 00:14:08.956
[thwack]

92
00:14:09.039 --> 00:14:11.125
[gasps]

93
00:14:12.710 --> 00:14:15.295
What. Mary? What is it?

94
00:14:21.426 --> 00:14:23.512
Listen...

95
00:14:24.846 --> 00:14:29.768
"Why is this night different
from every other night?"

96
00:14:35.065 --> 00:14:39.652
"Because once we were slaves.
and we are slaves no longer..."

97
00:14:43.406 --> 00:14:45.325
- [door rattles]
- Agh!

98
00:14:45.408 --> 00:14:47.493
[pants]

99
00:14:49.996 --> 00:14:52.081
They've seized him.

100
00:14:54.375 --> 00:14:55.710
- [thwack]
- Agh!

101
00:14:55.793 --> 00:14:57.879
[soldiers laugh and chatter]

102
00:15:01.507 --> 00:15:02.550
[thwack]

103
00:15:04.385 --> 00:15:05.928
[gasps]

104
00:15:06.011 --> 00:15:08.097
[labored breaths]

105
00:15:15.479 --> 00:15:17.564
[footsteps recede]

106
00:15:19.566 --> 00:15:21.652
[soldiers chatter and laugh]

107
00:15:23.362 --> 00:15:25.364
- [thwack]
- [grunts]

108
00:15:25.447 --> 00:15:27.366
Agh!

109
00:15:29.785 --> 00:15:31.870
- [thwack]
- [grunts]

110
00:15:33.455 --> 00:15:34.831
[chains rattle]

111
00:15:34.915 --> 00:15:36.833
- [grunts]
- [gasps]

112
00:15:36.917 --> 00:15:39.002
[prolonged groan]

113
00:15:57.186 --> 00:15:59.272
[metallic rattle]

114
00:16:01.399 --> 00:16:03.484
[soldiers laugh]

115
00:16:06.737 --> 00:16:09.240
[animal-like guttural groaning]

116
00:16:12.451 --> 00:16:14.411
[screeches]

117
00:16:14.495 --> 00:16:16.580
[raps loudly]

118
00:16:20.084 --> 00:16:22.169
[baby cries]

119
00:16:22.252 --> 00:16:26.965
Everyone you can. hear?
To the courtyard of the High Priest.

120
00:16:27.049 --> 00:16:29.134
Quick! Go!

121
00:16:38.310 --> 00:16:41.062
- [soldiers shout]
- [chains rattle]

122
00:16:45.066 --> 00:16:47.152
[pants]

123
00:16:51.781 --> 00:16:53.491
[fire crackles]

124
00:16:53.575 --> 00:16:55.660
[general hubbub]

125
00:17:04.085 --> 00:17:06.170
[muttering]

126
00:17:10.466 --> 00:17:12.551
[ominous music]

127
00:17:22.102 --> 00:17:24.229
[shouts orders]

128
00:17:48.503 --> 00:17:50.588
[staff clacks]

129
00:17:59.305 --> 00:18:01.849
Halt! Not so fast.

130
00:18:01.933 --> 00:18:04.769
This is not your party.
you toothless vermin.

131
00:18:11.484 --> 00:18:13.569
Peter...

132
00:18:16.656 --> 00:18:18.741
Peter...

133
00:18:23.996 --> 00:18:27.458
What's going on here?

134
00:18:27.541 --> 00:18:30.044
In there! Stop them!

135
00:18:30.127 --> 00:18:32.755
They've arrested him!

136
00:18:32.838 --> 00:18:35.340
In secret! In the night!

137
00:18:35.424 --> 00:18:38.010
To hide their crime from you!

138
00:18:38.385 --> 00:18:42.597
- Stop them!
- What are you yelling about. woman?

139
00:18:42.681 --> 00:18:45.016
Who have they arrested?

140
00:18:45.100 --> 00:18:46.643
Jesus.

141
00:18:46.726 --> 00:18:48.520
Jesus of Nazareth!

142
00:18:48.603 --> 00:18:51.439
Shut up!

143
00:18:51.523 --> 00:18:53.608
Shut up!

144
00:18:54.859 --> 00:18:57.070
Huh.

145
00:18:57.153 --> 00:18:58.321
She's crazy.

146
00:18:58.405 --> 00:19:04.285
A criminal.
Brought in for questioning. that's all.

147
00:19:04.369 --> 00:19:07.288
Broke the temple laws.

148
00:19:16.214 --> 00:19:18.466
I see...

149
00:19:18.549 --> 00:19:23.471
Better go tell him
there's more trouble brewing.

150
00:19:23.554 --> 00:19:25.765
Tell who?

151
00:19:25.848 --> 00:19:28.267
Abenader. you idiot.

152
00:19:28.350 --> 00:19:30.436
Get going!

153
00:19:31.687 --> 00:19:33.188
Go!

154
00:19:33.272 --> 00:19:35.357
[horse snorts]

155
00:19:43.991 --> 00:19:46.076
[metallic clunking]

156
00:19:56.503 --> 00:19:58.588
[dull thud]

157
00:20:02.467 --> 00:20:04.552
[blows]

158
00:20:16.022 --> 00:20:18.107
Jesus...

159
00:20:19.942 --> 00:20:21.986
Jesus?

160
00:20:22.069 --> 00:20:24.155
[grunts]

161
00:20:29.618 --> 00:20:31.704
[tapping]

162
00:20:35.040 --> 00:20:37.126
Are you hungry?

163
00:20:38.544 --> 00:20:40.629
Yes. I am.

164
00:20:48.595 --> 00:20:51.431
This is certainly a tall table!

165
00:20:53.016 --> 00:20:55.936
- Who is it for?
- A rich man.

166
00:20:57.979 --> 00:21:01.608
Does he like to eat standing up?

167
00:21:01.691 --> 00:21:05.779
[chuckles]
No. He prefers to eat like... so.

168
00:21:08.239 --> 00:21:11.117
Tall table. tall chairs.

169
00:21:11.910 --> 00:21:13.995
Well. I haven't made them yet.

170
00:21:27.717 --> 00:21:29.802
[chuckles]

171
00:21:30.594 --> 00:21:33.305
This will never catch on.

172
00:21:33.389 --> 00:21:35.433
Oh. no. you don't.

173
00:21:35.516 --> 00:21:38.811
Take off that dirty apron
before you come in.

174
00:21:41.188 --> 00:21:43.565
And wash your hands.

175
00:21:46.026 --> 00:21:47.986
[giggles]

176
00:21:48.070 --> 00:21:50.155
[background chatter]

177
00:21:59.790 --> 00:22:01.875
[soldier shouts orders]

178
00:22:10.800 --> 00:22:12.886
It has begun. Lord.

179
00:22:16.890 --> 00:22:18.975
So be it.

180
00:22:21.769 --> 00:22:23.855
[woman sobs]

181
00:22:36.951 --> 00:22:39.036
[woman sobs]

182
00:22:39.120 --> 00:22:41.205
[knock on door]

183
00:22:48.754 --> 00:22:50.089
[gasps]

184
00:22:50.172 --> 00:22:51.673
Sir. there's trouble at...

185
00:22:51.757 --> 00:22:54.134
What. in the middle of the night.
Abenader?

186
00:22:54.218 --> 00:22:56.929
- I'm sorry.
- What's the problem?

187
00:22:57.012 --> 00:22:59.389
Trouble within the walls.

188
00:22:59.473 --> 00:23:02.851
Caiphas had some prophet arrested.

189
00:23:02.934 --> 00:23:04.519
Who?

190
00:23:04.603 --> 00:23:06.646
Some Galilean.

191
00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:09.357
The Pharisees apparently hate the man.

192
00:23:09.441 --> 00:23:13.194
A Galilean? Who are you talking about?

193
00:23:13.278 --> 00:23:16.573
- [crowd jeers]
- Who is this beggar you bring to us.

194
00:23:16.656 --> 00:23:19.576
chained up like a condemned man?

195
00:23:20.577 --> 00:23:24.163
- He's Jesus. the Nazarene troublemaker!
- [gasps]

196
00:23:25.915 --> 00:23:28.001
You're Jesus of Nazareth?

197
00:23:29.627 --> 00:23:32.171
They say you're a king.

198
00:23:33.089 --> 00:23:35.258
Where is this kingdom of yours?

199
00:23:35.341 --> 00:23:38.135
What line of kings do you descend from?

200
00:23:38.844 --> 00:23:41.555
Speak up!

201
00:23:41.639 --> 00:23:45.017
You're just the son
of some obscure carpenter. no?

202
00:23:45.100 --> 00:23:46.644
[distant laughter]

203
00:23:46.727 --> 00:23:48.812
Some say you're Elijah.

204
00:23:49.939 --> 00:23:52.775
But he was carried off
to heaven in a chariot!

205
00:23:54.193 --> 00:23:56.278
Why don't you say something?

206
00:23:57.571 --> 00:24:02.284
You've been brought here
as a blasphemer!

207
00:24:03.535 --> 00:24:06.038
What do you say to that?

208
00:24:06.121 --> 00:24:08.206
Defend yourself.

209
00:24:08.290 --> 00:24:10.375
[crowd mutters]

210
00:24:13.295 --> 00:24:15.964
I have spoken openly to everyone.

211
00:24:17.048 --> 00:24:24.222
I've taught in the temple
where we all gather.

212
00:24:24.305 --> 00:24:27.850
Ask those who have heard
what I have to say.

213
00:24:27.934 --> 00:24:30.937
Is that how
you address the high priest?

214
00:24:31.813 --> 00:24:33.898
Hmm? With arrogance?

215
00:24:35.399 --> 00:24:37.485
- [thwack]
- [chains rattle]

216
00:24:37.568 --> 00:24:39.654
[crowd gasps]

217
00:24:48.329 --> 00:24:50.414
If I have spoken evil...

218
00:24:50.498 --> 00:24:53.959
...tell me what evil I have said.

219
00:24:54.043 --> 00:24:58.130
But if not. why do you hit me?

220
00:25:01.216 --> 00:25:04.970
Yes. we'll listen to those
who heard your blasphemies.

221
00:25:05.053 --> 00:25:07.139
Good!

222
00:25:07.222 --> 00:25:08.807
[scattered laughter]

223
00:25:08.890 --> 00:25:11.309
Let's hear them.

224
00:25:11.393 --> 00:25:14.438
He cures the sick by magic.

225
00:25:15.522 --> 00:25:17.607
With the help of devils!

226
00:25:18.984 --> 00:25:21.611
I've seen it.

227
00:25:21.695 --> 00:25:26.574
He casts out devils.
with the help of devils!

228
00:25:26.658 --> 00:25:28.743
[crowd laughs]

229
00:25:31.704 --> 00:25:36.376
He calls himself the king of the Jews!

230
00:25:38.419 --> 00:25:41.798
No. he calls himself the son of God!

231
00:25:41.881 --> 00:25:45.384
He said he would destroy the temple...

232
00:25:45.468 --> 00:25:49.221
...and rebuild it in three days.

233
00:25:49.305 --> 00:25:50.598
[spits]

234
00:25:50.681 --> 00:25:53.476
Worse! Worse!

235
00:25:53.559 --> 00:25:56.437
He claims he's the bread of life!

236
00:25:56.520 --> 00:26:02.109
And if we don't eat his flesh
or drink his blood...

237
00:26:02.192 --> 00:26:05.529
- ...we won't inherit eternal life.
- [crowd shouts]

238
00:26:05.612 --> 00:26:08.282
- Silence!
- [crowd falls silent]

239
00:26:08.365 --> 00:26:11.785
You're all under this man's spell.

240
00:26:12.536 --> 00:26:16.164
Either offer proof of his wrongdoing...

241
00:26:16.248 --> 00:26:20.377
...or be quiet!

242
00:26:21.711 --> 00:26:25.966
This entire proceeding is an outrage.

243
00:26:26.633 --> 00:26:31.554
All I've heard from these witnesses is
mindless contradiction!

244
00:26:31.638 --> 00:26:33.723
[crowd shouts]

245
00:26:43.608 --> 00:26:46.360
Who called this meeting anyway?

246
00:26:47.320 --> 00:26:49.697
And at this hour of the night?

247
00:26:49.780 --> 00:26:53.284
Where are the other members
of the council?

248
00:26:53.367 --> 00:26:55.453
Get him out of here!

249
00:26:56.162 --> 00:26:57.997
[woman] Get out!

250
00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:01.917
A travesty!
That's what this is. a beastly travesty!

251
00:27:09.800 --> 00:27:11.885
Haven't you anything to say?

252
00:27:13.303 --> 00:27:15.389
No answer to these accusations?

253
00:27:17.516 --> 00:27:21.269
I ask you now...

254
00:27:22.938 --> 00:27:25.565
...Jesus of Nazareth...

255
00:27:25.649 --> 00:27:30.111
Tell us. are you the Messiah?

256
00:27:31.571 --> 00:27:35.241
The son of the living God?

257
00:27:47.211 --> 00:27:49.297
I am...

258
00:27:50.423 --> 00:27:54.802
...and you will see the Son of Man
seated at the right hand of power

259
00:27:54.885 --> 00:27:56.971
and coming on the clouds of heaven.

260
00:27:57.054 --> 00:27:59.140
[crowd gasps and mutters]

261
00:28:01.892 --> 00:28:03.978
Blasphemy!

262
00:28:04.895 --> 00:28:06.438
Agh!

263
00:28:06.522 --> 00:28:12.236
You heard him.
There's no need for witnesses!

264
00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:18.534
Your verdict. What is your verdict?

265
00:28:18.617 --> 00:28:20.702
Death!

266
00:28:20.786 --> 00:28:22.287
[crowd shouts in agreement]

267
00:28:29.669 --> 00:28:31.421
- [thwack]
- [spits]

268
00:28:39.679 --> 00:28:40.972
[spits]

269
00:28:41.055 --> 00:28:43.141
[thwack]

270
00:28:44.934 --> 00:28:46.352
[thwack]

271
00:28:46.436 --> 00:28:48.521
[manic laughter]

272
00:28:51.232 --> 00:28:53.317
[shouts orders]

273
00:28:54.735 --> 00:28:56.821
[thwacking]

274
00:29:15.255 --> 00:29:18.675
Haven't I seen you in the company
of the Galilean?

275
00:29:18.759 --> 00:29:21.512
Yes! You're one of his disciples!

276
00:29:22.387 --> 00:29:24.473
I recognize you!

277
00:29:24.556 --> 00:29:27.893
Quiet! I've never met the man.
I don't know him.

278
00:29:27.976 --> 00:29:34.149
You are Peter!
One of the disciples of Jesus.

279
00:29:36.026 --> 00:29:39.946
- I don't know the man! You are wrong!
- [thwacking continues]

280
00:29:40.030 --> 00:29:43.742
- Stop! Stop!
- I've seen you before!

281
00:29:43.825 --> 00:29:46.453
Stop him! He's one of them!

282
00:29:47.412 --> 00:29:50.623
You're wrong. damn you!

283
00:29:51.499 --> 00:29:54.377
I swear I don't know the man.

284
00:29:55.169 --> 00:29:58.548
I've never seen him before.

285
00:30:07.139 --> 00:30:14.021
Wherever you go. Lord. I will follow.

286
00:30:15.940 --> 00:30:20.778
To prison. even to death.

287
00:30:24.948 --> 00:30:27.034
Amen. I say to you...

288
00:30:29.661 --> 00:30:31.747
...before the cock crows...

289
00:30:35.459 --> 00:30:37.544
...three times you will deny me.

290
00:30:46.886 --> 00:30:48.972
[sobs]

291
00:30:56.187 --> 00:30:58.272
[metallic rattle]

292
00:30:59.816 --> 00:31:01.526
[gasps]

293
00:31:01.609 --> 00:31:03.694
Peter? Peter?

294
00:31:11.952 --> 00:31:14.038
[Peter sobs]

295
00:31:18.459 --> 00:31:22.588
No. no... I am unworthy!

296
00:31:23.464 --> 00:31:26.550
I have denied him. Mother!

297
00:31:28.177 --> 00:31:31.889
Denied him three times.

298
00:31:34.558 --> 00:31:36.643
Three times!

299
00:31:42.190 --> 00:31:43.608
Three times!

300
00:31:43.692 --> 00:31:48.363
Let's go! You take care of it.

301
00:31:48.446 --> 00:31:50.532
[Judas shouts]

302
00:31:51.783 --> 00:31:54.160
Let him pass. He's harmless.

303
00:31:56.579 --> 00:31:58.665
Release him.

304
00:32:00.083 --> 00:32:02.460
Take back the silver.

305
00:32:02.543 --> 00:32:04.629
Here!

306
00:32:05.838 --> 00:32:09.258
I've sinned. betrayed innocent blood.

307
00:32:12.678 --> 00:32:17.391
Take back your silver. I don't want it!

308
00:32:17.475 --> 00:32:23.689
If you think you've betrayed
innocent blood. that's your affair.

309
00:32:23.772 --> 00:32:25.858
Take your money and go.

310
00:32:27.359 --> 00:32:28.777
Now go.

311
00:32:28.861 --> 00:32:30.946
[mutters]

312
00:32:32.948 --> 00:32:35.033
[coins clatter]

313
00:32:39.371 --> 00:32:41.456
[child calls out]

314
00:32:45.377 --> 00:32:47.462
[donkey brays]

315
00:32:55.470 --> 00:32:57.555
What's wrong? Are you all right?

316
00:32:57.639 --> 00:33:00.433
Look at his mouth.
Hey. can we look at it?

317
00:33:00.517 --> 00:33:03.353
You need help? Can we help?

318
00:33:03.436 --> 00:33:07.023
He's bleeding! Look! Blood!

319
00:33:07.899 --> 00:33:10.943
Leave me alone...

320
00:33:12.028 --> 00:33:14.697
- you little satans!
- [gasps]

321
00:33:14.780 --> 00:33:17.950
Aha! Cursing! Are you cursed?

322
00:33:18.034 --> 00:33:19.869
He's cursed!

323
00:33:19.952 --> 00:33:23.080
Yes. a curse! It's inside him. look!

324
00:33:23.164 --> 00:33:25.541
A curse. a curse!

325
00:33:25.624 --> 00:33:27.418
Agh!

326
00:33:27.501 --> 00:33:30.671
[boys] Aaagh!

327
00:33:30.754 --> 00:33:33.257
- [bones crunch]
- Argh!

328
00:33:33.340 --> 00:33:36.510
Watch out.
it's like burning oil from his bones!

329
00:33:36.593 --> 00:33:38.595
[boys shout]

330
00:33:38.679 --> 00:33:40.097
- [gasps]
- [shouts]

331
00:33:40.180 --> 00:33:42.182
[evil laugh]

332
00:33:42.266 --> 00:33:44.893
- [evil laugh]
- Get away from me! Leave me alone!

333
00:33:44.977 --> 00:33:47.062
[boys shouting]

334
00:33:54.736 --> 00:33:56.821
[hushed chatter]

335
00:34:23.264 --> 00:34:25.349
[Biblical music]

336
00:35:02.552 --> 00:35:04.637
[gentle sigh]

337
00:35:21.195 --> 00:35:23.281
[rattling]

338
00:35:26.993 --> 00:35:29.078
[water drips slowly]

339
00:35:31.288 --> 00:35:33.374
[gentle sigh]

340
00:35:46.637 --> 00:35:48.722
[children shouting]

341
00:35:51.225 --> 00:35:53.310
Argh!

342
00:35:57.773 --> 00:35:59.858
Agh!

343
00:36:01.443 --> 00:36:04.905
Agh! Agh!

344
00:36:07.991 --> 00:36:10.076
Aargh!

345
00:36:10.160 --> 00:36:12.245
[dramatic music]

346
00:36:19.377 --> 00:36:21.504
Agh!

347
00:36:21.587 --> 00:36:23.673
Agh! Agh!

348
00:36:33.683 --> 00:36:35.768
Aargh!

349
00:36:37.353 --> 00:36:39.438
[rapid breaths]

350
00:37:02.669 --> 00:37:04.754
[flies buzz]

351
00:37:19.769 --> 00:37:21.854
[loud buzzing]

352
00:37:26.734 --> 00:37:28.820
[sobs]

353
00:37:47.922 --> 00:37:50.007
[rope creaks]

354
00:38:04.646 --> 00:38:08.108
Don't condemn this Galilean.

355
00:38:08.191 --> 00:38:10.277
He's holy.

356
00:38:10.360 --> 00:38:12.946
You will only bring trouble on yourself.

357
00:38:13.029 --> 00:38:16.157
Do you want to know my idea of trouble.
Claudia?

358
00:38:16.241 --> 00:38:19.911
This stinking outpost.
that filthy rabble out there.

359
00:38:19.994 --> 00:38:22.080
[crowd shouts]

360
00:38:28.670 --> 00:38:30.755
[chains rattle]

361
00:39:04.496 --> 00:39:07.791
Do you always punish your prisoners
before they're judged?

362
00:39:07.874 --> 00:39:08.959
Governor...

363
00:39:09.042 --> 00:39:11.670
What accusations do you bring
against this man?

364
00:39:12.838 --> 00:39:14.881
Well...

365
00:39:14.965 --> 00:39:19.344
If he weren't a malefactor. we
wouldn't have brought him before you.

366
00:39:19.427 --> 00:39:21.805
That's not what I asked.

367
00:39:21.888 --> 00:39:24.224
Why don't you judge him
according to your own laws?

368
00:39:24.307 --> 00:39:31.439
Consul. you know it's unlawful for us
to condemn any man to death.

369
00:39:32.815 --> 00:39:34.025
To death?

370
00:39:34.108 --> 00:39:38.071
What has this man done
to merit such a penalty?

371
00:39:38.154 --> 00:39:41.240
- He has violated our Sabbath. Consul.
- [crowd murmurs]

372
00:39:42.283 --> 00:39:43.367
Go on.

373
00:39:43.451 --> 00:39:47.079
He has seduced the people...

374
00:39:47.872 --> 00:39:50.875
...taught foul. disgusting doctrines.

375
00:39:50.958 --> 00:39:54.795
Isn't he the prophet you welcomed
into Jerusalem only five days ago?

376
00:39:54.879 --> 00:39:59.633
And now you want him dead? Can
any of you explain this madness to me?

377
00:39:59.717 --> 00:40:01.802
[crowd shouts]

378
00:40:07.432 --> 00:40:11.228
Your Excellency...
Your Excellency. please...

379
00:40:12.813 --> 00:40:17.901
So far the high priest hasn't told you
this man's greatest crime.

380
00:40:18.944 --> 00:40:25.200
He is the leader of dangerous sect
who hail him as the Son of David.

381
00:40:26.785 --> 00:40:31.206
He claims that he is the Messiah...

382
00:40:31.289 --> 00:40:34.209
...the king promised to the Jews.

383
00:40:35.543 --> 00:40:40.882
He has forbidden his followers
to pay tribute to the emperor. Consul!

384
00:40:47.388 --> 00:40:49.473
Bring him here!

385
00:40:51.892 --> 00:40:53.227
[chains rattle]

386
00:40:53.310 --> 00:40:55.396
Let's go!

387
00:41:04.947 --> 00:41:07.032
[crowd shouts]

388
00:41:21.088 --> 00:41:23.173
Go!

389
00:41:27.969 --> 00:41:30.055
Drink.

390
00:41:42.483 --> 00:41:44.819
Are you the king of the Jews?

391
00:41:48.197 --> 00:41:50.283
Does this question come from you?

392
00:41:51.242 --> 00:41:56.038
Or do you ask me this because others
have told you that is what I am?

393
00:41:57.581 --> 00:42:01.961
Why would I ask you that?

394
00:42:02.044 --> 00:42:03.796
Am I a Jew?

395
00:42:03.879 --> 00:42:08.884
Your high priests. your own people
delivered you up to me.

396
00:42:09.551 --> 00:42:14.014
They want me to have you executed.
Why? What have you done?

397
00:42:16.558 --> 00:42:18.644
Are you a king?

398
00:42:22.606 --> 00:42:25.901
My kingdom is not of this world.

399
00:42:25.984 --> 00:42:32.282
If it were. do you think my followers
would have let them hand me over?

400
00:42:32.365 --> 00:42:35.744
Then you are a king?

401
00:42:38.163 --> 00:42:40.248
That is why I was born.

402
00:42:41.666 --> 00:42:43.751
To give testimony to the truth.

403
00:42:44.752 --> 00:42:50.008
All men who hear the truth hear my voice.

404
00:42:52.135 --> 00:42:54.220
Truth.

405
00:42:57.848 --> 00:42:59.934
What is truth?

406
00:43:01.727 --> 00:43:03.813
[crowd chatters]

407
00:43:16.283 --> 00:43:18.368
[chains rattle]

408
00:43:26.126 --> 00:43:30.338
I have questioned this prisoner.
and I find no cause in him.

409
00:43:30.422 --> 00:43:32.507
[crowd jeers]

410
00:43:41.182 --> 00:43:43.852
This man is a Galilean. is he not?

411
00:43:43.935 --> 00:43:45.937
He is.

412
00:43:46.020 --> 00:43:47.856
Then he is King Herod's subject.

413
00:43:47.939 --> 00:43:50.483
Let Herod judge him.

414
00:43:50.566 --> 00:43:52.819
- Governor...
- Hand him over.

415
00:43:52.902 --> 00:43:54.987
- [chains jangle]
- [crowd shouts]

416
00:44:12.213 --> 00:44:14.298
Ah. ah. ah.

417
00:44:16.300 --> 00:44:18.594
Jesus of Nazareth.

418
00:44:18.677 --> 00:44:20.763
Where?

419
00:44:25.017 --> 00:44:27.102
Where is he?

420
00:44:33.275 --> 00:44:35.360
This...

421
00:44:36.695 --> 00:44:38.321
...is Jesus of Nazareth?

422
00:44:38.405 --> 00:44:40.991
- [replies]
- Nah-nah.

423
00:44:44.285 --> 00:44:47.664
Is it true
that you restore sight to the blind?

424
00:44:50.875 --> 00:44:52.877
Raise men from the dead?

425
00:44:52.961 --> 00:44:55.088
[groans]

426
00:44:55.171 --> 00:44:57.256
[drunken laughter]

427
00:45:09.894 --> 00:45:13.272
Where do you get your power?

428
00:45:19.612 --> 00:45:24.366
Are you the one
whose birth was foretold?

429
00:45:31.957 --> 00:45:34.459
Answer me.

430
00:45:34.543 --> 00:45:36.628
Are you a king?

431
00:45:41.091 --> 00:45:46.930
How about me?
Will you work a little miracle for me?

432
00:46:00.193 --> 00:46:02.278
[laughs]

433
00:46:04.447 --> 00:46:06.532
Take this stupid fool out of my sight.

434
00:46:07.909 --> 00:46:11.412
He's not guilty of a crime.
he's just crazy.

435
00:46:13.205 --> 00:46:15.833
Give him a fool's homage...
[metallic clatter]

436
00:46:15.916 --> 00:46:18.419
- [crowd laughs]
- Ow!

437
00:46:19.837 --> 00:46:22.131
[low growl]

438
00:46:38.814 --> 00:46:40.899
What is truth. Claudia?

439
00:46:40.983 --> 00:46:45.695
Do you hear it.
recognize it when it is spoken?

440
00:46:46.863 --> 00:46:48.990
Yes. I do.

441
00:46:51.660 --> 00:46:53.286
- Don't you?
- How?

442
00:46:55.205 --> 00:46:57.290
Can you tell me?

443
00:47:06.174 --> 00:47:10.303
If you will not hear the truth.
no one can tell you.

444
00:47:12.930 --> 00:47:15.016
Truth...

445
00:47:16.142 --> 00:47:19.103
Do you want to know what my truth is.
Claudia?

446
00:47:19.186 --> 00:47:24.275
I've been putting down rebellions
in this rotten outpost for eleven years.

447
00:47:26.485 --> 00:47:32.241
If I don't condemn this man.
I know Caiphas will start a rebellion.

448
00:47:32.324 --> 00:47:36.912
If I do condemn him.
then his followers may.

449
00:47:36.995 --> 00:47:39.581
Either way. there will be bloodshed.

450
00:47:40.499 --> 00:47:43.543
Caesar has warned me. Claudia.
Warned me twice.

451
00:47:44.127 --> 00:47:47.589
He swore that the next time
the blood would be mine.

452
00:47:47.672 --> 00:47:49.758
That is my truth!

453
00:47:49.841 --> 00:47:51.927
[man's voice]

454
00:47:55.305 --> 00:48:00.560
Herod refuses to condemn the man.
They're bringing him back here.

455
00:48:00.643 --> 00:48:03.605
We're going to need reinforcements.

456
00:48:03.688 --> 00:48:06.191
I don't want to cause an uprising.

457
00:48:06.274 --> 00:48:09.027
There is already an uprising.

458
00:48:09.777 --> 00:48:11.863
[marching footsteps]

459
00:48:15.533 --> 00:48:17.618
[crowd roars]

460
00:48:19.620 --> 00:48:21.706
[rattles]

461
00:48:35.261 --> 00:48:39.098
- King Herod found no cause in this man.
- [crowd silent]

462
00:48:40.974 --> 00:48:43.060
Neither do I.

463
00:48:43.143 --> 00:48:45.729
[crowd shout in disagreement]

464
00:48:50.275 --> 00:48:54.446
Men! Attend to the crowd!

465
00:49:03.496 --> 00:49:05.582
Quiet!

466
00:49:05.915 --> 00:49:07.667
Quiet!

467
00:49:07.750 --> 00:49:11.087
Have you no respect
for our Roman procurator?

468
00:49:11.170 --> 00:49:13.256
[crowd laughs]

469
00:49:18.761 --> 00:49:23.391
As you know. every year
I release a criminal back to you.

470
00:49:24.183 --> 00:49:28.354
We are now holding a notorious murderer...

471
00:49:28.437 --> 00:49:30.523
- Barabbas.
- [chains rattle]

472
00:49:33.317 --> 00:49:35.402
[crowd shouts]

473
00:49:40.157 --> 00:49:42.242
[groans]

474
00:49:42.826 --> 00:49:44.912
[guttural choking]

475
00:49:46.830 --> 00:49:49.625
Which of the two men
would you have me release to you?

476
00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:52.252
The murderer Barabbas?

477
00:49:52.336 --> 00:49:54.421
Or Jesus. called the Messiah?

478
00:49:54.504 --> 00:49:59.259
He is not the Messiah!
He is an imposter! A blasphemer!

479
00:50:00.343 --> 00:50:02.429
Free Barabbas!

480
00:50:02.512 --> 00:50:04.598
[crowd shout in agreement]

481
00:50:08.393 --> 00:50:10.478
[laughs]

482
00:50:18.444 --> 00:50:24.075
Again I ask you: which of these two men
should I release to you?!

483
00:50:24.158 --> 00:50:27.245
- [man] Free Barabbas!
- [crowd chants "Free Barabbas"]

484
00:50:30.790 --> 00:50:32.875
[manic laugh]

485
00:50:42.426 --> 00:50:44.511
Free him.

486
00:50:46.764 --> 00:50:48.849
[manic laugh]

487
00:51:04.739 --> 00:51:07.325
- Hey!
- [crowd cheers]

488
00:51:11.287 --> 00:51:13.373
Ha!

489
00:51:14.457 --> 00:51:16.543
- Hey!
- [crowd gasps]

490
00:51:18.002 --> 00:51:21.422
What would you have me do
with Jesus the Nazarene?

491
00:51:22.507 --> 00:51:24.592
Have him crucified!

492
00:51:24.676 --> 00:51:26.761
[crowd shouts in agreement]

493
00:51:30.264 --> 00:51:32.350
[all chant] Have him crucified!

494
00:51:40.066 --> 00:51:41.525
No!

495
00:51:41.609 --> 00:51:43.819
I will chastise him...

496
00:51:43.903 --> 00:51:45.988
...but then I will set him free.

497
00:51:46.071 --> 00:51:48.157
[crowd jeers]

498
00:51:50.159 --> 00:51:53.078
See to it that the punishment is severe.
Abenader.

499
00:51:53.162 --> 00:51:56.623
But don't let them kill the man.

500
00:52:00.043 --> 00:52:02.129
[chains rattle]

501
00:52:16.851 --> 00:52:18.937
[laughs]

502
00:52:24.067 --> 00:52:26.152
[soldiers chatter]

503
00:52:33.868 --> 00:52:35.953
Silence!

504
00:52:36.412 --> 00:52:38.581
Ooh. Mmm-mmm-mmm.

505
00:52:38.664 --> 00:52:40.750
[drunken laughter and chatter]

506
00:52:42.543 --> 00:52:46.005
Dah! Aargh!

507
00:52:46.088 --> 00:52:48.174
[drunken laughter]

508
00:53:18.495 --> 00:53:20.580
My heart is ready. Father...

509
00:53:21.289 --> 00:53:23.375
...my heart is ready.

510
00:53:30.965 --> 00:53:33.051
- [whack]
- [crowd gasps]

511
00:53:33.718 --> 00:53:35.803
- [whack]
- [groans]

512
00:53:37.180 --> 00:53:39.265
- [whack]
- [groans]

513
00:53:40.808 --> 00:53:42.894
- [whack]
- [soldier grunts]

514
00:53:44.020 --> 00:53:46.105
[whack]

515
00:53:47.398 --> 00:53:49.483
- [whack]
- [Jesus groans]

516
00:53:50.734 --> 00:53:52.778
- [thwack]
- [groans]

517
00:53:52.862 --> 00:53:54.947
[whacking continues]

518
00:53:55.906 --> 00:53:57.616
[chuckles]

519
00:53:57.700 --> 00:53:59.451
- [soldier grunts]
- [thwack]

520
00:53:59.535 --> 00:54:01.620
[gasps]

521
00:54:02.121 --> 00:54:04.206
- [soldier grunts]
- whack]

522
00:54:04.873 --> 00:54:07.167
[thwack]

523
00:54:07.251 --> 00:54:08.710
More!

524
00:54:08.794 --> 00:54:10.879
[whack]

525
00:54:11.922 --> 00:54:13.215
[groans]

526
00:54:13.298 --> 00:54:14.925
- 14!
- [thwack]

527
00:54:15.008 --> 00:54:16.218
- 15!
- [thwack]

528
00:54:16.301 --> 00:54:17.552
- 16!
- [thwack]

529
00:54:17.636 --> 00:54:19.137
[Jesus gasps]

530
00:54:19.221 --> 00:54:21.181
- 18!
- [thwack]

531
00:54:21.264 --> 00:54:23.683
- 19!
- [thwack]

532
00:54:23.767 --> 00:54:26.519
- 20!
- [all mutter]

533
00:54:27.979 --> 00:54:30.440
- 21!
- [thwack]

534
00:54:30.523 --> 00:54:33.067
- 22!
- [Jesus cries out]

535
00:54:33.151 --> 00:54:35.236
- 23!
- [thwack]

536
00:54:35.570 --> 00:54:37.280
[grunts]

537
00:54:37.363 --> 00:54:39.449
- 24!
- [whack]

538
00:54:44.245 --> 00:54:46.330
- 25!
- [whack]

539
00:54:48.082 --> 00:54:50.167
- 26!
- [whack]

540
00:54:51.752 --> 00:54:53.838
- 27!
- [whack]

541
00:54:56.715 --> 00:54:58.801
- 28!
- [whack]

542
00:54:58.884 --> 00:54:59.969
[groans]

543
00:55:00.052 --> 00:55:02.137
- 29!
- [whack]

544
00:55:02.221 --> 00:55:03.430
[grunts]

545
00:55:03.514 --> 00:55:05.766
- 30!
- [whack]

546
00:55:05.849 --> 00:55:07.810
[crowd mutters]

547
00:55:07.893 --> 00:55:09.520
[speaks]

548
00:55:09.603 --> 00:55:11.688
31!

549
00:55:12.523 --> 00:55:14.107
- 32!
- [whack]

550
00:55:14.191 --> 00:55:16.276
Enough!

551
00:55:17.277 --> 00:55:19.363
[groans]

552
00:55:42.218 --> 00:55:44.303
[grunts]

553
00:55:45.763 --> 00:55:47.849
[hushed chatter]

554
00:55:48.724 --> 00:55:50.810
[soldiers chatter]

555
00:55:54.897 --> 00:55:56.315
[grunts]

556
00:55:56.399 --> 00:55:58.484
[soldiers laugh]

557
00:56:10.621 --> 00:56:12.706
No.

558
00:56:19.212 --> 00:56:21.298
[rattles]

559
00:56:26.178 --> 00:56:28.263
- [soldier grunts]
- [rattles]

560
00:56:29.681 --> 00:56:32.809
- [both shout]
- [soldiers laugh]

561
00:56:40.692 --> 00:56:42.777
[labored breaths]

562
00:56:51.369 --> 00:56:53.204
- [soldier grunts]
- [whack]

563
00:56:53.287 --> 00:56:55.790
Agh!

564
00:56:55.873 --> 00:56:57.959
- [whack]
- [loud gasp]

565
00:57:01.253 --> 00:57:03.339
[whack]

566
00:57:03.422 --> 00:57:04.632
- Four!
- [gasps]

567
00:57:04.715 --> 00:57:06.800
- Five!
- [gasps]

568
00:57:07.593 --> 00:57:10.262
- Six!
- Agh!

569
00:57:10.346 --> 00:57:12.431
[crowd murmurs]

570
00:57:13.557 --> 00:57:15.976
- Seven!
- [gasps]

571
00:57:16.060 --> 00:57:17.436
[sharp intake of breath]

572
00:57:17.519 --> 00:57:19.605
- Eight!
- [thwack]

573
00:57:21.607 --> 00:57:23.692
[soldiers laugh drunkenly]

574
00:57:26.862 --> 00:57:28.488
- [thwack]
- Agh!

575
00:57:28.572 --> 00:57:29.823
"Agh!"

576
00:57:29.906 --> 00:57:31.908
- Nine!
- [rattle]

577
00:57:31.992 --> 00:57:33.577
- [squelch]
- Aargh!

578
00:57:33.660 --> 00:57:35.495
[gasps]

579
00:57:35.579 --> 00:57:37.664
[soldiers laugh]

580
00:57:39.708 --> 00:57:41.793
[flogging continues]

581
00:57:47.298 --> 00:57:49.384
My son...

582
00:57:50.551 --> 00:57:54.889
...when. where. how...

583
00:57:57.683 --> 00:58:01.354
...will you choose
to be delivered of this?

584
00:58:05.566 --> 00:58:08.194
- 16!
- [drunken laughter]

585
00:58:08.277 --> 00:58:10.070
- 17!
- [loud squelch]

586
00:58:10.154 --> 00:58:13.199
- 18!
- [loud squelch]

587
00:58:13.282 --> 00:58:15.367
[laughs]

588
00:58:17.328 --> 00:58:19.038
- 19!
- [metallic rattle]

589
00:58:19.121 --> 00:58:20.164
[groans]

590
00:58:20.247 --> 00:58:22.332
- 20!
- [whack]

591
00:58:22.791 --> 00:58:24.543
21!

592
00:58:24.626 --> 00:58:26.712
22!

593
00:58:28.672 --> 00:58:31.049
- [sobs]
- 23!

594
00:58:31.133 --> 00:58:33.218
[gasps]

595
00:58:34.845 --> 00:58:36.930
- 24!
- [whack]

596
00:58:43.186 --> 00:58:45.271
[distant whip cracks]

597
00:59:17.845 --> 00:59:19.930
[whack]

598
00:59:20.306 --> 00:59:22.391
[whack]

599
00:59:34.528 --> 00:59:36.613
[sobs]

600
00:59:36.697 --> 00:59:38.782
[flogging continues]

601
01:00:34.962 --> 01:00:37.339
- [thwack]
- [Jesus] Agh!

602
01:00:37.422 --> 01:00:39.508
Stop.

603
01:00:54.856 --> 01:00:56.941
[groans]

604
01:01:07.952 --> 01:01:09.954
Eight!
[squelch]

605
01:01:10.037 --> 01:01:12.165
- Nine!
- [thwack]

606
01:01:12.248 --> 01:01:14.292
- Ten!
- [thwack]

607
01:01:14.375 --> 01:01:16.460
[grunts]

608
01:01:19.797 --> 01:01:22.216
- [dream-like]
- [whip cracks]

609
01:01:22.299 --> 01:01:24.385
[choral music]

610
01:01:37.898 --> 01:01:39.983
[gasps]

611
01:02:04.507 --> 01:02:06.593
[gasps]

612
01:02:07.302 --> 01:02:09.387
[metallic rattle]

613
01:02:10.430 --> 01:02:12.515
[gasps]

614
01:02:22.775 --> 01:02:24.860
If the world hates you...

615
01:02:25.903 --> 01:02:33.202
...remember that it has hated me first.

616
01:02:36.705 --> 01:02:39.833
Remember also that no servant
is greater than his master.

617
01:02:41.627 --> 01:02:47.215
If they persecuted me.
they will persecute you.

618
01:02:49.009 --> 01:02:51.094
You must not be afraid.

619
01:02:51.178 --> 01:02:53.263
The Helper will come...

620
01:02:55.515 --> 01:02:58.685
...who reveals the truth about God...

621
01:03:02.147 --> 01:03:04.441
...and who comes from the Father.

622
01:03:10.238 --> 01:03:12.657
- [whack]
- [gasps]

623
01:03:12.740 --> 01:03:14.826
Stop!

624
01:03:16.494 --> 01:03:20.623
Enough!
Your orders were to punish this man...

625
01:03:23.834 --> 01:03:26.712
...not to scourge him to death!

626
01:03:29.882 --> 01:03:32.760
[labored breaths and groans]

627
01:03:33.511 --> 01:03:35.596
Take him away.

628
01:03:37.973 --> 01:03:40.059
Get going!

629
01:03:42.144 --> 01:03:44.229
[metallic jangle]

630
01:03:44.354 --> 01:03:46.440
- [gentle thud]
- [gasps]

631
01:03:48.483 --> 01:03:50.569
Get him out of here!

632
01:03:55.699 --> 01:03:57.784
[grunts]

633
01:03:59.035 --> 01:04:01.121
[groans]

634
01:04:59.511 --> 01:05:00.721
[sobs]

635
01:05:15.110 --> 01:05:18.988
- [groans gently]
- [soldiers laugh]

636
01:05:21.908 --> 01:05:23.993
Your majesty...

637
01:05:24.077 --> 01:05:26.287
Take care of it.

638
01:05:26.370 --> 01:05:28.456
A beautiful rose bush.

639
01:05:28.539 --> 01:05:30.625
[gasps]

640
01:05:31.876 --> 01:05:35.421
Look at him... king of the worms!

641
01:05:35.504 --> 01:05:36.547
[laughs]

642
01:05:36.630 --> 01:05:40.426
Hail. wormy king!

643
01:05:40.509 --> 01:05:42.928
- A color fit for a king!
- [gasps]

644
01:05:43.012 --> 01:05:45.681
[soldiers laugh]

645
01:05:45.764 --> 01:05:47.850
- [thwack]
- [groans]

646
01:06:16.336 --> 01:06:18.421
[echo reverberates]

647
01:06:27.472 --> 01:06:29.557
[crunching]

648
01:06:49.034 --> 01:06:51.120
[hollow thuds]

649
01:07:09.846 --> 01:07:11.932
[jewelry tinkling]

650
01:07:54.390 --> 01:07:56.475
Ohh...

651
01:07:58.018 --> 01:08:00.104
- [whack]
- [soldiers laugh drunkenly]

652
01:08:00.187 --> 01:08:02.272
We're here to pay our respects.

653
01:08:03.774 --> 01:08:06.485
A leader for our brotherhood!

654
01:08:12.407 --> 01:08:14.493
[general hubbub]

655
01:08:26.171 --> 01:08:28.256
[gasps]

656
01:08:39.517 --> 01:08:41.602
[labored breaths]

657
01:08:45.481 --> 01:08:47.566
[crowd gasps]

658
01:08:56.033 --> 01:08:59.787
Behold the man.

659
01:09:00.704 --> 01:09:03.165
Crucify him!

660
01:09:03.248 --> 01:09:05.334
[crowd chant "crucify him"]

661
01:09:14.009 --> 01:09:16.720
Isn't this enough? Look at him!

662
01:09:16.803 --> 01:09:19.973
- Crucify him!
- [crowd chant "crucify him!"

663
01:09:21.600 --> 01:09:23.685
[gasps and moans]

664
01:09:33.111 --> 01:09:35.196
Shall I crucify your king?

665
01:09:36.447 --> 01:09:39.367
We have no king but Caesar!

666
01:09:41.744 --> 01:09:43.788
Speak to me.

667
01:09:43.871 --> 01:09:47.583
I have the power to crucify you.
or else to set you free.

668
01:09:50.002 --> 01:09:52.421
[labored breaths]

669
01:09:52.505 --> 01:09:56.425
You have no power over me.

670
01:09:56.509 --> 01:10:01.305
except what is given you from above.

671
01:10:04.141 --> 01:10:09.688
Therefore. it is he who
delivered me to you

672
01:10:10.189 --> 01:10:12.858
who has the greater sin.

673
01:10:13.609 --> 01:10:20.782
If you free him. Governor.
you are no friend of Caesar's.

674
01:10:23.201 --> 01:10:26.371
- You must crucify him!
- [crowd chant "crucify him!"

675
01:10:36.005 --> 01:10:38.091
[whack]

676
01:10:41.511 --> 01:10:42.679
Agh!

677
01:10:42.762 --> 01:10:44.639
[clicks fingers]

678
01:10:45.556 --> 01:10:48.101
- [shouts out orders]
- [whispers]

679
01:10:51.854 --> 01:10:53.940
[thwack]

680
01:10:54.857 --> 01:10:56.025
Agh!

681
01:10:56.108 --> 01:10:58.194
[woman screams]

682
01:11:06.494 --> 01:11:08.579
[labored grunts]

683
01:11:42.821 --> 01:11:44.906
[crowd shouts]

684
01:11:57.210 --> 01:12:02.173
It is you who want to crucify him. not I.
Look you to it.

685
01:12:02.256 --> 01:12:04.342
I am innocent of this man's blood.

686
01:12:08.429 --> 01:12:10.514
[crowd chants "crucify him"]

687
01:12:23.861 --> 01:12:25.946
Abenader...

688
01:12:30.158 --> 01:12:32.244
Do as they wish.

689
01:12:33.453 --> 01:12:35.539
[woman shouts]

690
01:12:46.549 --> 01:12:48.635
[soldier shouts orders]

691
01:12:49.552 --> 01:12:51.638
[loud creak]

692
01:13:06.527 --> 01:13:10.573
I am your servant. Father. Your servant.
and the son of your handmaid.

693
01:13:10.656 --> 01:13:17.913
Why do you embrace your cross. fool?!

694
01:13:21.542 --> 01:13:24.378
All right. your highness. let's move!

695
01:13:24.461 --> 01:13:26.547
Let's move!

696
01:13:27.589 --> 01:13:28.632
- [whack]
- Agh!

697
01:13:34.554 --> 01:13:36.640
[crowd shouts]

698
01:13:52.155 --> 01:13:54.157
[wooden creaking]

699
01:13:54.240 --> 01:13:56.451
- [dream-like]
- [crowd shouts]

700
01:13:59.329 --> 01:14:01.414
[groans]

701
01:14:01.497 --> 01:14:03.583
[labored breaths]

702
01:14:10.506 --> 01:14:13.009
[fronds rustle]

703
01:14:13.092 --> 01:14:14.885
- [whip cracks]
- Argh!

704
01:14:23.852 --> 01:14:25.938
[gasps]

705
01:14:51.004 --> 01:14:53.089
[wooden creaking]

706
01:14:59.012 --> 01:15:01.639
Help me get near him.

707
01:15:05.059 --> 01:15:08.521
This way.

708
01:15:10.815 --> 01:15:12.900
[clunking]

709
01:15:16.445 --> 01:15:18.531
[wooden creaking]

710
01:15:22.660 --> 01:15:25.079
[loud thud]

711
01:15:25.162 --> 01:15:27.248
[dramatic music]

712
01:15:36.548 --> 01:15:38.634
[thwack]

713
01:15:40.719 --> 01:15:42.804
[thwack]

714
01:15:47.309 --> 01:15:49.394
[groans]

715
01:15:56.818 --> 01:15:59.028
This way. Mother.

716
01:16:08.288 --> 01:16:10.373
[thwack]

717
01:16:11.791 --> 01:16:13.876
[crowd shouts out]

718
01:16:15.169 --> 01:16:17.255
[gasps]

719
01:16:19.173 --> 01:16:21.258
[soldier shouts orders]

720
01:16:38.484 --> 01:16:40.569
Mother...

721
01:16:45.407 --> 01:16:47.492
[crowd jeering]

722
01:16:56.334 --> 01:16:58.420
[gentle gasp]

723
01:16:58.753 --> 01:17:01.297
- [dream-like]
- [whip cracks and crowd jeers]

724
01:17:09.055 --> 01:17:11.474
- [loud thud]
- [gasps]

725
01:17:15.061 --> 01:17:16.687
Ah! Ah!

726
01:17:25.780 --> 01:17:27.865
[gasps]

727
01:17:28.032 --> 01:17:30.284
[creaks and thuds]

728
01:17:30.367 --> 01:17:32.453
[grunts]

729
01:17:32.912 --> 01:17:34.622
[Mary] Ohh!

730
01:17:34.705 --> 01:17:36.790
[gasps]

731
01:17:40.919 --> 01:17:43.005
Mother...

732
01:17:59.312 --> 01:18:01.398
[gasps]

733
01:18:16.120 --> 01:18:18.206
[sobs]

734
01:18:18.873 --> 01:18:20.958
I'm here...

735
01:18:24.128 --> 01:18:26.214
I'm here...

736
01:18:35.055 --> 01:18:39.768
See. Mother. I make all things new.

737
01:19:09.381 --> 01:19:11.466
Let's go.

738
01:19:11.549 --> 01:19:13.635
- Who is that?
- Who?

739
01:19:15.512 --> 01:19:17.597
She's the Galilean's mother.

740
01:19:17.680 --> 01:19:19.766
Let's go.

741
01:19:21.809 --> 01:19:23.895
Come on!

742
01:19:26.731 --> 01:19:28.816
[whinnies]

743
01:19:34.113 --> 01:19:36.699
- [thwack]
- [solider] Move!

744
01:19:36.782 --> 01:19:38.868
- [loud groan]
- [women gasp]

745
01:19:44.790 --> 01:19:47.209
[soldiers shout out orders
and whip cracks]

746
01:19:49.586 --> 01:19:51.672
- [women sob]
- [loud thud]

747
01:19:53.799 --> 01:19:55.884
[thwacking continues]

748
01:19:59.471 --> 01:20:01.556
[groans]

749
01:20:04.184 --> 01:20:06.269
[gasps]

750
01:20:07.312 --> 01:20:09.648
[birdsong]

751
01:20:09.731 --> 01:20:11.816
[distant crowd shouting and jeering]

752
01:20:26.664 --> 01:20:28.750
[sobs gently]

753
01:20:33.671 --> 01:20:35.923
Don't fret. my daughter.

754
01:20:36.007 --> 01:20:38.092
Don't fret.

755
01:20:47.476 --> 01:20:49.562
[soldiers shout orders]

756
01:20:51.522 --> 01:20:53.607
[loud thud]

757
01:20:56.276 --> 01:20:58.362
[groans]

758
01:21:00.405 --> 01:21:02.491
[soldiers shout orders and laugh]

759
01:21:03.533 --> 01:21:05.619
[shouts orders]

760
01:21:08.663 --> 01:21:10.707
Are you blind?

761
01:21:10.791 --> 01:21:13.627
Can't you see. he can't go on?

762
01:21:18.173 --> 01:21:20.258
Help him!

763
01:21:24.137 --> 01:21:26.222
[gasps and groans]

764
01:21:34.313 --> 01:21:36.399
[child sobs]

765
01:21:39.193 --> 01:21:41.070
You!

766
01:21:41.153 --> 01:21:45.825
Yes. you! Get over here.

767
01:21:51.205 --> 01:21:53.290
What do you want from me?

768
01:21:53.374 --> 01:21:57.044
This criminal can't carry his cross
by himself anymore.

769
01:21:57.127 --> 01:21:59.338
You will help him! Now get going!

770
01:21:59.421 --> 01:22:04.718
I can't do that. It's none of my business.
Get someone else.

771
01:22:04.801 --> 01:22:07.429
Help him! He is a holy man.

772
01:22:07.512 --> 01:22:09.640
Do as I tell you. Now move! Let's go!

773
01:22:14.269 --> 01:22:17.397
All right. but I'm an innocent man.

774
01:22:17.480 --> 01:22:20.859
forced to carry the cross
of a condemned man.

775
01:22:21.860 --> 01:22:24.696
Stay here. Wait for me.

776
01:22:37.166 --> 01:22:39.252
[creaking]

777
01:22:47.385 --> 01:22:49.470
[groans]

778
01:22:55.684 --> 01:22:57.770
[grunts]

779
01:22:57.853 --> 01:22:59.939
[labored breaths]

780
01:23:07.905 --> 01:23:09.990
[groans]

781
01:23:15.954 --> 01:23:17.914
[whinnies]

782
01:23:17.998 --> 01:23:20.083
[soldier shout orders]

783
01:23:20.542 --> 01:23:22.627
[thwack]

784
01:23:23.837 --> 01:23:25.922
[thwack]

785
01:23:27.716 --> 01:23:29.759
[loud thud]

786
01:23:29.843 --> 01:23:31.928
[grunts]

787
01:23:44.315 --> 01:23:46.484
- [dream-like]
- [crowd noise recedes]

788
01:24:20.517 --> 01:24:23.395
Permit me. my Lord.

789
01:24:40.286 --> 01:24:42.372
[groans]

790
01:24:50.338 --> 01:24:53.049
- [soldier shouts]
- [gasps]

791
01:24:53.132 --> 01:24:59.847
Who do you think you are?
Get away from here.

792
01:24:59.930 --> 01:25:01.474
[thwack]

793
01:25:01.557 --> 01:25:03.642
Impossible people!

794
01:25:06.687 --> 01:25:08.480
[spits]

795
01:25:08.564 --> 01:25:10.983
- [thwack]
- [soldiers laugh]

796
01:25:11.066 --> 01:25:13.569
Someone stop this!

797
01:25:15.529 --> 01:25:17.614
[thwack]

798
01:25:19.491 --> 01:25:21.577
[soldiers laugh drunkenly]

799
01:25:29.584 --> 01:25:34.130
Stop! Stop!

800
01:25:35.131 --> 01:25:38.385
Stop! Stop!

801
01:25:39.094 --> 01:25:43.097
- [drunken laughter]
- Leave him alone!

802
01:25:51.022 --> 01:25:55.860
If you don't stop.
I won't carry that cross one more step.

803
01:25:55.943 --> 01:25:59.322
I don't care what you do to me!

804
01:26:04.618 --> 01:26:07.746
All right. all right. let's get moving.

805
01:26:07.830 --> 01:26:11.000
We don't have all day. Let's go!

806
01:26:17.214 --> 01:26:19.591
Let's go...

807
01:26:19.675 --> 01:26:21.760
...Jew!

808
01:26:21.969 --> 01:26:24.054
[wooden thud]

809
01:26:32.437 --> 01:26:34.523
[soldier shout orders]

810
01:26:42.655 --> 01:26:44.741
[shouts]

811
01:27:03.634 --> 01:27:05.720
[thwack]

812
01:27:25.823 --> 01:27:27.699
[sobs]

813
01:27:27.783 --> 01:27:29.868
[crowd jeers and shouts]

814
01:27:33.163 --> 01:27:35.082
[grunts]

815
01:27:35.165 --> 01:27:37.250
[women gasp and sob]

816
01:27:49.220 --> 01:27:51.306
[neighs]

817
01:27:51.389 --> 01:27:53.474
[hooves thunder]

818
01:28:05.069 --> 01:28:07.154
[hammering]

819
01:28:13.369 --> 01:28:15.454
[groans]

820
01:28:28.759 --> 01:28:30.844
[dream-like]

821
01:28:36.099 --> 01:28:38.185
[moans]

822
01:28:43.648 --> 01:28:45.734
[groans]

823
01:28:49.195 --> 01:28:51.281
[wooden creak]

824
01:28:53.700 --> 01:28:55.994
- [dream-like]
- [soldier shouts orders]

825
01:28:59.247 --> 01:29:01.332
Almost there.

826
01:29:07.797 --> 01:29:09.882
We're nearly there.

827
01:29:23.479 --> 01:29:27.441
Almost done.

828
01:29:36.909 --> 01:29:40.954
You have heard it said...

829
01:29:42.539 --> 01:29:46.751
...you shall love your neighbor
and hate your enemy.

830
01:29:46.835 --> 01:29:48.920
But I say to you...

831
01:29:50.755 --> 01:29:55.802
...love your enemies and pray for those
who persecute you.

832
01:29:58.388 --> 01:30:00.974
For if you love only those who love you...

833
01:30:05.436 --> 01:30:07.522
...what reward is there in that?

834
01:30:09.065 --> 01:30:11.150
[dramatic music]

835
01:30:14.946 --> 01:30:17.031
[gasps]

836
01:30:21.243 --> 01:30:23.329
[soldier shouts orders]

837
01:30:26.081 --> 01:30:28.167
[groans]

838
01:30:50.689 --> 01:30:52.774
[hammering continues]

839
01:30:53.358 --> 01:30:54.609
[gasps]

840
01:30:56.903 --> 01:30:58.989
[shouts orders]

841
01:31:04.911 --> 01:31:06.996
I am the good shepherd.

842
01:31:08.206 --> 01:31:10.291
I lay down my life for my sheep.

843
01:31:11.459 --> 01:31:14.087
No one takes my life from me...

844
01:31:15.379 --> 01:31:17.840
...but I lay it down of my own accord.

845
01:31:17.924 --> 01:31:20.301
I have power to lay it down...

846
01:31:20.384 --> 01:31:23.387
...and power to take it up again.

847
01:31:26.557 --> 01:31:28.684
This command is from my Father.

848
01:31:33.606 --> 01:31:35.691
[grunts]

849
01:31:39.153 --> 01:31:41.363
[loud thud]

850
01:31:41.447 --> 01:31:43.949
[grunts]

851
01:31:44.032 --> 01:31:46.118
[groans]

852
01:31:47.911 --> 01:31:50.080
Aaaaagh!

853
01:32:09.098 --> 01:32:14.062
[soldier] Get away now. you're free to go.
Go on! Go on!

854
01:32:21.277 --> 01:32:24.655
- You can get up now!
- [labored breaths]

855
01:32:31.162 --> 01:32:33.247
[soldier shouts orders]

856
01:32:37.209 --> 01:32:39.295
[crowd shouts]

857
01:32:55.686 --> 01:32:57.771
[sobs]

858
01:32:59.523 --> 01:33:01.608
[panting]

859
01:33:04.152 --> 01:33:07.072
Get up. your majesty.

860
01:33:08.406 --> 01:33:10.492
Can't you get up?

861
01:33:11.701 --> 01:33:15.163
We haven't got all day. [laughs]

862
01:33:23.296 --> 01:33:25.673
Come on. move! We're ready.

863
01:33:25.757 --> 01:33:27.842
Get up. your highness.

864
01:33:36.475 --> 01:33:38.561
- [dream-like]
- [soldier shouts]

865
01:33:45.651 --> 01:33:47.736
[soldiers laugh]

866
01:34:33.281 --> 01:34:35.366
- [soldiers laugh]
- [ripping]

867
01:34:43.541 --> 01:34:45.626
[soldier shout orders]

868
01:35:10.984 --> 01:35:13.069
You are my friends.

869
01:35:15.155 --> 01:35:19.784
There is no greater love than for a man
to lay down his life for his friends.

870
01:35:22.370 --> 01:35:24.455
[soldiers laugh and shout]

871
01:35:24.539 --> 01:35:26.624
[sobs]

872
01:35:34.257 --> 01:35:36.342
[moans]

873
01:35:36.968 --> 01:35:38.010
[gasps]

874
01:35:38.094 --> 01:35:40.179
[crowd shouts]

875
01:35:49.939 --> 01:35:52.024
[dramatic music]

876
01:36:17.549 --> 01:36:21.594
I cannot be with you much longer.
my friends.

877
01:36:21.678 --> 01:36:26.391
You cannot go where I am going.

878
01:36:27.433 --> 01:36:30.478
My commandment to you
after I am gone is this...

879
01:36:32.730 --> 01:36:35.858
Love one another.

880
01:36:35.942 --> 01:36:42.865
As I have loved you.
so love one another.

881
01:36:48.621 --> 01:36:50.206
- [squelch]
- [gasps]

882
01:36:50.289 --> 01:36:52.374
[whack]

883
01:36:54.919 --> 01:36:56.754
[gasps]

884
01:36:56.837 --> 01:36:59.089
[whack]

885
01:36:59.173 --> 01:37:01.050
- [whack]
- [sobs]

886
01:37:01.133 --> 01:37:03.218
[whacking continues]

887
01:37:05.721 --> 01:37:07.806
You believe in me.

888
01:37:12.436 --> 01:37:15.772
You know that I am the Way.

889
01:37:15.856 --> 01:37:20.402
the Truth. and the Life.

890
01:37:22.737 --> 01:37:25.907
And no one comes to the Father
but by me.

891
01:37:29.119 --> 01:37:31.204
[sobs]

892
01:37:32.288 --> 01:37:34.374
Further out...

893
01:37:36.125 --> 01:37:38.211
[moans]

894
01:37:41.005 --> 01:37:45.009
Idiots! Let me show you how to do it.

895
01:37:45.092 --> 01:37:47.178
Like this!

896
01:37:47.803 --> 01:37:49.889
[groans]

897
01:37:52.433 --> 01:37:54.518
[rope creaks]

898
01:37:56.937 --> 01:37:59.023
[grunts]

899
01:38:00.482 --> 01:38:01.901
- [bone cracks]
- [gasps]

900
01:38:05.029 --> 01:38:09.867
There! No. get in there.
Hold the hand open like this.

901
01:38:09.950 --> 01:38:12.703
Father. forgive them...

902
01:38:15.038 --> 01:38:17.124
- [metallic clunk]
- [grunts]

903
01:38:18.208 --> 01:38:20.293
[clunks]

904
01:38:21.837 --> 01:38:24.172
- [clunk]
- [gasps]

905
01:38:24.256 --> 01:38:26.341
[loud sobs]

906
01:38:27.425 --> 01:38:29.052
[clunk]

907
01:38:29.135 --> 01:38:31.221
[clunk]

908
01:38:35.975 --> 01:38:38.061
[groans]

909
01:38:49.405 --> 01:38:51.490
[metallic clunking]

910
01:38:51.574 --> 01:38:53.659
[whinnies]

911
01:38:55.995 --> 01:38:58.080
[both laugh]

912
01:39:00.040 --> 01:39:02.042
- [bone cracks]
- Argh!

913
01:39:02.126 --> 01:39:08.465
Father. Father. my Father... my God...

914
01:39:10.009 --> 01:39:12.302
[clunking continues]

915
01:39:12.386 --> 01:39:15.722
They don't know... they don't know...

916
01:39:15.806 --> 01:39:17.891
[squelches]

917
01:39:19.643 --> 01:39:25.732
Stupid mongrels! Turn the wood over
on its face. idiots!

918
01:39:28.902 --> 01:39:30.987
- [wooden creak]
- [groans]

919
01:39:37.327 --> 01:39:39.412
[coughs and splutters]

920
01:39:41.539 --> 01:39:43.625
- Agh!
- [Jesus gasps]

921
01:39:43.708 --> 01:39:45.793
- [soldiers laugh]
- [dripping]

922
01:39:48.755 --> 01:39:50.465
Ohh.

923
01:39:50.548 --> 01:39:52.633
[groans]

924
01:40:05.896 --> 01:40:07.982
[metallic clunks]

925
01:40:24.414 --> 01:40:26.500
[clatters]

926
01:40:32.005 --> 01:40:33.048
Agh!

927
01:40:33.131 --> 01:40:35.217
[wooden creaking]

928
01:40:41.973 --> 01:40:43.683
- [loud thud]
- Argh!

929
01:40:43.767 --> 01:40:45.852
[soldiers laugh]

930
01:40:48.771 --> 01:40:50.857
[metallic clunks]

931
01:40:53.776 --> 01:41:01.075
Take this and eat. This is my body
which is given up for you.

932
01:41:02.952 --> 01:41:04.370
[groans]

933
01:41:04.453 --> 01:41:06.539
[dramatic music]

934
01:41:56.129 --> 01:41:58.214
[gentle clatter]

935
01:42:04.679 --> 01:42:06.764
[gasps]

936
01:42:09.475 --> 01:42:10.935
[loud creak]

937
01:42:11.018 --> 01:42:12.561
[gasps]

938
01:42:12.645 --> 01:42:14.730
[groans]

939
01:42:26.033 --> 01:42:28.118
[metallic clank]

940
01:42:31.580 --> 01:42:33.665
[dream-like laughter]

941
01:42:45.760 --> 01:42:49.806
Take this and drink.

942
01:42:51.224 --> 01:42:53.935
This is my blood of the new covenant...

943
01:42:54.018 --> 01:42:59.107
...which is given for you and for many.
for the forgiveness of sins.

944
01:42:59.190 --> 01:43:01.275
Do this in memory of me.

945
01:43:15.623 --> 01:43:17.708
[labored breaths]

946
01:43:23.672 --> 01:43:25.758
[man shouts]

947
01:43:30.054 --> 01:43:36.393
If you are the son of God.
why don't you save yourself?

948
01:43:37.769 --> 01:43:44.818
Prove to us you are
who you say you are.

949
01:43:45.444 --> 01:43:47.529
[groans]

950
01:43:50.615 --> 01:43:52.701
[laughter and chatter]

951
01:44:03.086 --> 01:44:09.300
You said you could destroy the temple
and rebuild it in three days...

952
01:44:09.884 --> 01:44:14.055
.and yet you cannot come down
from that cross.

953
01:44:14.138 --> 01:44:16.807
If he is the Messiah...

954
01:44:16.891 --> 01:44:22.730
...I say let him
come down from the cross...

955
01:44:22.813 --> 01:44:25.733
...so that we may see and believe.

956
01:44:25.816 --> 01:44:27.902
[crowd shouts in agreement]

957
01:44:35.492 --> 01:44:39.037
Father. forgive them...

958
01:44:41.081 --> 01:44:45.293
...they know not what they do.

959
01:44:49.923 --> 01:44:52.008
Listen...

960
01:44:52.926 --> 01:44:55.011
He prays for you.

961
01:45:11.361 --> 01:45:16.699
We deserve this. Gesmas.
but he does not.

962
01:45:19.869 --> 01:45:25.958
I have sinned.
and my punishment is just.

963
01:45:26.625 --> 01:45:31.672
You would be justified
in condemning me.

964
01:45:32.673 --> 01:45:39.638
I ask only that you remember me. Lord.
when you enter your kingdom.

965
01:45:43.809 --> 01:45:50.649
Amen. I tell you.
on this day you shall be with me...

966
01:45:54.528 --> 01:45:56.613
...in paradise.

967
01:45:58.031 --> 01:46:00.116
[sobs]

968
01:46:00.909 --> 01:46:02.994
[manic laugh]

969
01:46:06.664 --> 01:46:08.750
[crow caws]

970
01:46:14.922 --> 01:46:16.424
- [squelch]
- Argh!

971
01:46:16.507 --> 01:46:18.301
- [squelch]
- Argh!

972
01:46:18.384 --> 01:46:20.470
- [caws]
- Argh!

973
01:46:42.366 --> 01:46:44.743
[thunderclap]

974
01:46:44.827 --> 01:46:46.912
[gasps]

975
01:46:50.040 --> 01:46:52.125
[thunderclap]

976
01:47:04.429 --> 01:47:06.931
[drunken laughter and chatter]

977
01:47:08.516 --> 01:47:10.602
[thunderclap]

978
01:47:18.109 --> 01:47:20.194
[rolling thunder]

979
01:47:34.667 --> 01:47:36.752
[rolling thunder]

980
01:47:38.712 --> 01:47:40.798
[loud thunderclap]

981
01:47:43.342 --> 01:47:45.427
[wind howls]

982
01:47:50.099 --> 01:47:52.184
[crowd shouts]

983
01:47:56.063 --> 01:47:58.148
[donkey brays]

984
01:48:02.903 --> 01:48:04.988
[rolling thunder]

985
01:48:06.448 --> 01:48:08.533
[wind howls]

986
01:48:11.786 --> 01:48:13.872
[sobs]

987
01:48:26.259 --> 01:48:28.344
[wind howls]

988
01:48:46.695 --> 01:48:48.781
[gentle groan]

989
01:48:51.533 --> 01:48:53.619
[sobs]

990
01:49:10.510 --> 01:49:12.596
I thirst.

991
01:49:47.546 --> 01:49:49.632
Flesh of my flesh...

992
01:49:50.424 --> 01:49:52.468
[groans]

993
01:49:52.551 --> 01:49:54.637
...heart of my heart...

994
01:49:55.929 --> 01:50:02.561
[gasps] My son. let me die with you.

995
01:50:06.064 --> 01:50:08.650
Woman....

996
01:50:08.734 --> 01:50:12.028
...behold your son.

997
01:50:16.700 --> 01:50:20.453
Son. behold...

998
01:50:27.043 --> 01:50:28.545
...your mother.

999
01:50:28.628 --> 01:50:30.713
[sobs]

1000
01:50:39.013 --> 01:50:41.098
There is no one left.

1001
01:50:43.142 --> 01:50:47.313
No one. Jesus!

1002
01:50:48.814 --> 01:50:50.900
[thunderclap]

1003
01:50:58.365 --> 01:51:00.451
My God...

1004
01:51:05.581 --> 01:51:07.666
My God...

1005
01:51:14.631 --> 01:51:16.716
...why have you forsaken me?

1006
01:51:26.184 --> 01:51:28.269
[wind whistles]

1007
01:51:37.362 --> 01:51:39.447
It is accomplished.

1008
01:51:41.491 --> 01:51:43.576
[sobs]

1009
01:51:52.752 --> 01:51:55.713
[gasps and exhales]

1010
01:51:58.299 --> 01:52:00.384
[labored breaths]

1011
01:52:02.344 --> 01:52:06.390
Father. into your hands...

1012
01:52:06.473 --> 01:52:10.519
I commend... my spirit.

1013
01:52:19.152 --> 01:52:22.489
[gentle sigh]

1014
01:52:44.052 --> 01:52:46.637
[loud splash]

1015
01:52:46.721 --> 01:52:48.848
[wind howls]

1016
01:52:48.931 --> 01:52:51.601
- [thunderclap]
- [soldiers shout]

1017
01:52:51.684 --> 01:52:53.769
- [neighs]
- [loud rumbling]

1018
01:53:04.363 --> 01:53:06.448
[rumbling and rattling]

1019
01:53:10.369 --> 01:53:12.287
[soldiers shout]

1020
01:53:12.371 --> 01:53:14.456
[metallic rattling]

1021
01:53:17.793 --> 01:53:19.544
[shouts orders]

1022
01:53:19.628 --> 01:53:21.713
[loud rumbling]

1023
01:53:25.801 --> 01:53:27.886
[rumbles and clatters]

1024
01:53:31.681 --> 01:53:33.767
[shouts orders]

1025
01:53:36.353 --> 01:53:38.438
Argh!

1026
01:53:46.029 --> 01:53:47.196
Aargh!

1027
01:53:47.280 --> 01:53:49.365
Aagh!

1028
01:53:52.201 --> 01:53:53.828
[whack]

1029
01:53:53.911 --> 01:53:55.997
Agh!

1030
01:54:01.252 --> 01:54:03.337
[loud rumble]

1031
01:54:03.546 --> 01:54:06.465
Cassius! Hurry!

1032
01:54:06.549 --> 01:54:08.634
He's dead!

1033
01:54:10.052 --> 01:54:12.137
Make sure!

1034
01:54:18.602 --> 01:54:20.687
[squelch]

1035
01:54:24.858 --> 01:54:26.943
Agh!

1036
01:55:04.522 --> 01:55:06.190
[clattering]

1037
01:55:06.273 --> 01:55:08.359
[sobs]

1038
01:55:17.951 --> 01:55:20.037
[screeches]

1039
01:57:22.990 --> 01:57:25.075
[low rumble]

1040
01:58:45.320 --> 01:58:47.406
[uplifting choral music]
